<item>
            <title>[QPID-6583] [Java Client] AMQSession_0_10 should use connection task pool rather than a Timer</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/QPID-6583</link>
                <project id="12310520" key="QPID">Qpid</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently the AMQSession_0_10 class uses a static time object to schedule ack flushing.  This leaves a thread running at all times even if all connections are closed.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In preference to this we can use the thread pool already associated with the connection to run the tasks currently run on the timer.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;See &lt;a href=&quot;http://mail-archives.apache.org/mod_mbox/qpid-users/201506.mbox/%3CCAJ2jEUtdc8mUV45Rm6XoZpj_1ZPo3n1R7GG4X%3DQtiy%2BoRbSfWw%40mail.gmail.com%3E&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;this mail&lt;/a&gt; for the issues that the current mechanism may cause.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
